Boil your #kettle{} and pour the water into a large #saucepan{} on high heat, with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

When boiling, stir in the @rigatoni pasta{180%g} and cook for ~{12%minutes}.

Drain in a #colander{}, pop back in the pan, drizzle with a little @oil{a little} and stir through to stop it sticking together. Leave to the side.

Meanwhile, trim the @courgette{1}, halve lengthways and slice into 1cm half moons.

Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1} (stalks and all).

Zest and halve the @lemon{1/2}, then peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{a drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Add the @diced chicken thigh{260%g}. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, cook until the chicken is browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling chicken and its packaging.

Add the courgette and cook until it starts to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the garlic and cook for another ~{1%minute}.

Reduce the heat and add the @water{100%ml} and @chicken stock paste{10%g} to the pan.

Stir in the @crème fraîche{150%g}, bring to a simmer and cook until the sauce has thickened slightly and the chicken is cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, mix together the lemon zest and parsley in a #small bowl{}.

Once the chicken is cooked, remove the pan with the sauce from the heat.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed and add a splash of water if the sauce is a bit thick.

Stir the drained pasta into the sauce.

Season with a squeeze of lemon juice to taste.

Mix well, then serve in #bowls{} topped with the lemon zest and parsley mix. Enjoy!